HEADWORD: Discerp
<hw>Dis*cerp"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>discerpere</ets>, <ets>discerptum</ets>; <ets>dis-</ets> +
<ets>carpere</ets> to pluck.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To tear in pieces;
to rend.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Stukeley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To separate; to disunite.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Bp. Hurd.</au></rj></p>

